erface.\n\n## Risks & Mitigations\n- **Incorrect bit‑width detection** – we gather all indices from both x and y wires and take the max + 1.\n- **Missing internal wires** – we only compare wires that actually exist in the circuit set.\n- **Performance** – enumeration limited to 5 bits (max 1024 combos) plus a bit of randomness; well within time limits.\n- **Cyclic circuits** – `simulate` throws if any gate cannot be resolved (should not happen per spec).\n\n## Next Steps\n- Write the implementation (already done).\n- Ensure TypeScript builds.\n- Run tests.\n- Update progress log.\n- Mark tasks completed.\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","title":".opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772755149763,"end":1772755149769}}}}
